originalText.text:
My wife went here for a routine cleaning but after being seen by the dentist, a finance worker came in explaining how much various unnecessary procedures would cost with no explanation from the dentist about whether or why any of these were needed. I've never heard of a dentist office sending in someone with no medical training to discuss procedures with you. They are trying to make money out of you by pulling the wool over your eyes, cramming down expensive procedures that insurance won't cover. Manipulative and unprofessional.

Also watch out as they will charge you for not canceling 2 days in advance. I would have had no idea if not for my wife telling me after her visit, so I went ahead and canceled mine. No transparency.
